\f1\fs32 The 
\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::4>
\f2\b\fs32 International Convention for the Safety of Life at Sea
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::4>
\f1\fs32  (SOLAS) is an international treaty developed by the 
\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::4>
\f2\b\fs32 International Maritime Organization
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::4>
\f1\fs32  (IMO) in 1914, following the sinking of the Titanic, one of the most famous maritime disasters in history.   \
SOLAS sets out minimum safety standards for the construction, equipment, and operation of ships in order to prevent accidents at sea and ensure that ships are well-prepared to handle emergencies. \
